      • validateSimpleKeys

        public static void validateSimpleKeys(java.lang.String... keys)
        To ensure that simple keys do not go into composite key namespace, we validate simple key to check whether the key starts with 0x00 (which is the namespace for compositeKey). This helps in avoding simple/composite key collisions.
        Throws:
        CompositeKeyFormatException - if First character of the key
